defaultThe majority of agricultural resources are not currently used to feed people, but instead are either used for animal feed, 
defaultagrofuels and other industrial commodities, or produce foods that are wasted. A redirection of these resources towards producing food for direct human consumption, in ways that are socially and environmentally sustainable would secure future food provision
default both in the UK and internationally
