default17
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultAgroecology is explained by UN Special Rapporteur 
defaulton
default the Right to Food, Olivier De Schutter as follows:
default“Agroecology is both a science and a set of pract
defaultices. It was created by the convergence of two scientific disciplines: agronomy and ecology. As a science, agroecology is the “application of ecological science to the study, design and management 
defaultof sustainable agroecosystems.
default” 
defaultAs a set of agricultural pr
defaultactices, agroecology seeks ways to enhance agricultural systems by mimicking natural processes, thus creating beneficial biological interactions and synergies among the components of the agroecosystem. It provides the most favourable soil conditions for pl
defaultant growth, particularly by managing organic matter and by raising soil biotic activity. The core principles of agroecology include recycling nutrients and energy on the farm, rather than introducing external inputs; integrating crops and livestock; divers
defaultifying species and genetic resources in agroecosystems over time and space; and focusing on interactions and productivity across the agricultural system, rather than focusing on individual species. Agroecology is highly knowledge-intensive, based on techni
defaultques that are not delivered top-down but developed on the basis of farmers’ knowledge and experimentation.”
default 
default18
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultInvestment and support in strengthening 
defaultand protecting 
defaultagroecological farming by small-scale food producers, in the framew
defaultork of food sovereignty, has the most potential for supporting livelihoods and rural communities, reducing poverty, 
defaultensuring access to food for vulnerable groups, 
defaultcreating resilient food systems, enabling people to have a healthy diet and regenerating the 
defaultenvironment. 
defaultThis in turn is important for enhancing peace, stability and prosperity worldwide.
