defaultEstimates suggest that between one third and one half of global food production is thrown away, wasting not only the food but also all the energy and resources that have gone into producing that food.
default 
defaultSome of the major culprits of food waste are
default inadequate storage and transport infrastructure, irresponsible consumption (buying more than is needed) and restrictive selection rules (as in the case of fruits that are only accepted by retailers if the fit some predetermined aesthetic characteristics).
default An
defaultother aspect of food waste that i
defaults usually not discussed is the one represented by the inefficiency of feeding human edible crops to animals instead
default of directly to people.
