default 
defaultThis would not only reduce the financial costs of meat production (animal feed costs have gone up markedly over recent years), but also greatly reduce the demand for very large amounts of soya and other crops for animal food, which in turn have enormous s
defaultocial and environmental impacts during production and processing – such as
