defaultLocally resilient food systems, incorporating adequate stocks of foods, can mitigate food price volatility. In contrast, the global industrialised commodity regime can exacerbate volatility. It is contro
defaultlled by a handful of corporations that dominate the development and marketing of inputs (agrochemicals, seed varieties and livestock genetics), commercialisation of products, transport, trade and retail. They may redirect investments towards agrofuels, cel
defaultlulose production, livestock feed or other commodities as subsidy 
