default35
default&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultSpeculation in commodity futures markets is creating volatile price movements that do not 
defaultreflect true changes in demand and supply. Position limits were used effectively in the US for most of the twentieth century to prevent market manipulation and excessive speculation, and are used on markets in Australia, Japan, Hong Kong, Singapore, China 
defaultand South Africa today. They are transparent and give traders legal certainty. The introduction of position limits could be a reduction in the opportunity cost of excessive speculation, through the diversion of capital into genuine, productive investment. 
defaultOn the issue of liquidity, the argument that position limits, if set too low, could damage liquidity for hedgers is redundant when current levels of financial speculation are so far above historic norms. The UK’s current self-regulatory approach has a trac
defaultk record of failure and creates conflicts of interest and a regulatory race-to-the-bottom.
default 
